    "### Advantages of Manhattan & Euclidean Distance\n",
    "\n",
    "- Symmetric: d(X, Y) = d(Y, X)\n",
    "- Non-negative\n",
    "- d(X, Y) = 0\n",
    "- Triangle inequality\n",
    "    - d(X, Y) <= d(X, Z) + d(Z, Y)\n",
    "- Ffunctions satisfying above are called metrics"
   ]
